<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="298" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source"><persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the
                                    Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SLA1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d298fn1">Sent to Washington via military channels,
                                    forwarded by the White House Map Room to the Department of
                                    State, and relayed by the Department to the Embassy at Ankara
                                    (740.0011 <gloss target="#t_EW1">EW</gloss>
                                1939/32811b).</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-24">24 November 1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>From the President to Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">Steinhardt</persName>, Ankara, Turkey. Personal and secret.</p>
                            <p>Our next plans have been advanced. Hope to see you in Cairo in about
                                a week,<note n="2" xml:id="d298fn2"><persName corresp="#p_SLA1">Steinhardt</persName> arrived in Cairo at 5 o’clock on the
                                    afternoon of the same day. See the Log, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_297">p. 297</ref>; see also <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_100">p.
                                    100</ref>.</note> and in regard to your number one<note n="3" xml:id="d298fn3">President <persName corresp="#p_II1">Inönü</persName> of Turkey. For subsequent correspondence
                                    regarding arrangements for <persName corresp="#p_II1">Inönü</persName> to come to Cairo, see <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_633">pp. 633</ref>, <ref target="#pg_662">662</ref>.</note> will advise you in a day
                                or two.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>